      "en": {
        "file": "35_autres_forces.md",
        "title": "柔劲 · róu jìn",
        "markdown": "## 柔劲 · róu jìn\n\n### The Soft Force\n\n---\n\n> Water never breaks.\n\n— Traditional saying\n\n---\n\n## The Essence of Róu Jìn\n\nRóu means soft, flexible, gentle, malleable.\n\nRóu Jìn is the force of ultimate softness. It does not resist, does not strike, does not force. It yields, embraces, circumvents, and yet it prevails.\n\nThe masters describe it as:\n\n· water that takes all forms,\n\n· silk that bends without ever breaking,\n\n· wind that passes through every obstacle.\n\n---\n\n## Fundamental Principles\n\n1\\. Softness is the absence of resistance\n\nRóu Jìn never creates direct conflict. It accepts the opponent's force, absorbs it, circumvents it. There is nothing against which to struggle.\n\n2\\. Softness is total adaptability\n\nRóu Jìn has no fixed form. It embraces the opponent's form, molds itself into his hollows, follows his lines.\n\n3\\. Softness contains power\n\nRóu Jìn is not weak. It is potential. Like water that can become a wave, softness can at any instant become explosion.\n\n4\\. Softness triumphs over hardness\n\nWhat is hard breaks. What is soft survives. Róu Jìn is the force that wins by adaptation, not by domination.\n\n---\n\n## Final Summary\n\nRóu Jìn is the force of water and wind. It strikes nothing, and nothing can strike it. It passes everywhere, adapts to everything, and always ends by traversing what resists it."
      },
      "zh": {
        "file": "35_autres_forces.md",
        "title": "柔劲 · róu jìn",
        "markdown": "## 柔劲 · róu jìn\n\n### The Soft Force\n\n**定义。** 柔劲是一种极度柔软、极度敏感的力量，如绵里藏针，外柔内刚，以柔克刚。\n\n**详细说明。** 柔劲不是弱、不是没力，而是极度灵活、极度变化的力。它如水、如云，无形无象，却无孔不入。\n\n**身体机制。** 全身极度放松，筋膜极度柔软，肌肉极度灵活。力量如绵绸，极度可变，极度灵活，随对方而变，随形而化。\n\n**练习。** 先练习极度放松，让身体如水一般柔软。然后在推手中，不用力，只是随对方而动，随形而化。\n\n**技击应用。** 对方猛攻时，用柔劲随其力量，不顶不挣，然后在其旧力已尽、新力未生之际，柔中突然吐出刚劲还击。\n\n**常见错误。** 柔而无力、僵而不活、只会退不会进、柔而无骨、被动而不主动。\n\n**掌握标志。** 身体极度柔软极度灵活，对方打来像打在海绵上，力量被吸收、被引导、被化解，然后突然被还击。"
      }
